WEBVTT

00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:11.200
[Amit Varma]: How did we get to episode 300? When I began the scene in the unseen almost 6 years ago,

00:00:11.200 --> 00:00:15.280
[Amit Varma]: it was an experiment. I didn't understand podcasting and this show was so different

00:00:15.280 --> 00:00:20.480
[Amit Varma]: then. But I kept myself open to learning and realised that all my priors about this medium

00:00:20.480 --> 00:00:25.240
[Amit Varma]: were wrong. I did not have to cater to short attention spans. People want depth, they want

00:00:25.240 --> 00:00:30.720
[Amit Varma]: nuance, they want serious discussion that is not about scoring points or gotcha moments.

00:00:30.720 --> 00:00:35.080
[Amit Varma]: And they are interested in human beings as much as ideas. Over this time, the show has

00:00:35.080 --> 00:00:40.160
[Amit Varma]: evolved from 20 minute glimpses of public policy to 2 hour deep dives into subjects

00:00:40.160 --> 00:00:45.160
[Amit Varma]: to 5 hour conversations that are akin to oral history. And the deeper my dives, the deeper

00:00:45.160 --> 00:00:49.340
[Amit Varma]: your engagement. So I want to thank all of you for the love you've given me which keeps

00:00:49.340 --> 00:00:53.880
[Amit Varma]: me going. This is not just a matter of great numbers. This show is kept alive and financially

00:00:53.880 --> 00:00:58.200
[Amit Varma]: viable by the contributions of listeners. To bring up an old trope of mine, your love

00:00:58.200 --> 00:01:03.320
[Amit Varma]: ain't just some abstract thing. It's concrete and I feel it every day. So thank you again.

00:01:03.320 --> 00:01:09.000
[Amit Varma]: Now, I celebrated episode 200 with a mega conversation curated by Shruti Rajgopalan,

00:01:09.000 --> 00:01:13.680
[Amit Varma]: in which a whole bunch of my guests asked me questions. For episode 300, I've decided

00:01:13.680 --> 00:01:18.280
[Amit Varma]: not to do something so elaborate, but just get a special guest. That's what I've done.

00:01:18.280 --> 00:01:25.880
[Unknown]: And we had a special conversation. Welcome to the scene and the unseen, our weekly

00:01:25.880 --> 00:01:35.640
[Unknown]: podcast on economics, politics and behavioral science. Please welcome your host, Amit Varma.

00:01:35.640 --> 00:01:39.840
[Amit Varma]: Welcome to the scene and the unseen. My guest today is Pratap Bhanu Mehta. And I was almost

00:01:39.840 --> 00:01:44.640
[Amit Varma]: tempted not to record the intro for this episode because Pratap needs no introduction. Pratap

